chunks.html_content: You may need to tell DVLA if you have had a heart transplant.
chunks.plain_content:
Heart transplants and driving
You may need to tell DVLA if you have had a heart transplant.

chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. If you’re involved in an accident, you may be prosecuted.
chunks.plain_content:
Heart transplants and driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. If you’re involved in an accident, you may be prosecuted.

chunks.html_content: You don’t need to tell DVLA, but you should stop driving for at least 1 month and only start driving again when your doctor tells you that you are safe to do so. Read leaflet ‘CLE1066’ for more information.
chunks.plain_content:
Heart transplants and driving
Car or motorcycle licence
You don’t need to tell DVLA, but you should stop driving for at least 1 month and only start driving again when your doctor tells you that you are safe to do so. Read leaflet ‘CLE1066’ for more information.

chunks.html_content: Download ‘CLE1066 - Car or motorcycle drivers with heart conditions’ (PDF, 129KB)

chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA. Fill in form VOCH1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
